</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=apprenhightowerr>Appren Hightowerr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#333333>(12/30/02 7:35:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1144.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tinkering.org/icon/ggnome1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Summoned vs. Purchased Equipment</span><hr size=1> I ALWAYS use the bracer, and in 99% of the cases ring, only time I dont use earring is when fighting dispelling mobs, as I need my gobbie skull earring then. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=99814" target="top">Master Appren Hightowerr</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
